@startuml
title SDGW TX Scheduler / Dispatcher
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "Producers" {
  [GsaClient\nfunctional command]
  [BpmClient\nfunctional command]
  [Internal sender]
  [SdGwLinkSupervisor\nping under silence]
}

package "Central arbitration" {
  [SdGwTxScheduler]
  [High queue]
  [Normal queue]
  [Low queue]
}

[GsaClient\nfunctional command] --> [High queue]
[BpmClient\nfunctional command] --> [High queue]
[Internal sender] --> [Normal queue]
[SdGwLinkSupervisor\nping under silence] --> [Low queue]

[High queue] --> [SdGwTxScheduler]
[Normal queue] --> [SdGwTxScheduler]
[Low queue] --> [SdGwTxScheduler]

[SdGwTxScheduler] --> [SdGwLinkEngine\nsingle stop-and-wait]
[SdGwLinkEngine\nsingle stop-and-wait] --> [SerialTransport]
[SerialTransport] --> [BPM / SggwLink]
[BPM / SggwLink] --> [GatewayApp / GwRouter]
[GatewayApp / GwRouter] --> [GSA]

note right of [SdGwTxScheduler]
Priority order:
1. High
2. Normal
3. Low

FIFO inside the same priority.
end note

note bottom of [SdGwLinkEngine\nsingle stop-and-wait]
Busy remains a technical safeguard,
but should not be the normal way to arbitrate
functional commands vs supervision.
end note
@enduml
